{"metadata":{"name":"Sunan Abu Dawud","section":{"3":{"eng-name":"The Book Of The Prayer For Rain (Kitab al-Istisqa')","ara-name":"كتاب الاستسقاء"}},"section_detail":{"3":{"hadithnumber_first":1161,"hadithnumber_last":1197,"arabicnumber_first":1161,"arabicnumber_last":1197}}},"hadiths":[{"hadithnumber":1171,"arabicnumber":1171,"text":"Narrated Anas:The Prophet (ﷺ) used to make supplication for rain in this manner. he spread his hands keeping the inner side (of hands) towards the earth, so I witnessed the whiteness of his armpits","grades":[{"name":"Al-Albani","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Muhammad Muhyi Al-Din Abdul Hamid","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Shuaib Al Arnaut","grade":"Sahih"},{"name":"Zubair Ali Zai","grade":"Sahih Muslim (896)"}],"reference":{"book":3,"hadith":11},"chapter":{"id":3,"ara-name":"باب رَفْعِ الْيَدَيْنِ فِي الاِسْتِسْقَاءِ","eng-name":"Raising The Hands During Istisqa'","isFirstHadith":false}}]}